{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":653,"text":"In the mid-'90s,"},{"time":2265,"text":"the CDC and Kaiser Permanente\n"},{"time":4872,"text":"discovered an exposure\nthat dramatically increased the risk"},{"time":8992,"text":"for seven out of 10 of the leading\ncauses of death in the United States."},{"time":14953,"text":"In high doses, it affects\nbrain development,"},{"time":18344,"text":"the immune system, hormonal systems,"},{"time":22011,"text":"and even the way our DNA\nis read and transcribed."},{"time":26684,"text":"Folks who are exposed in very high doses"},{"time":30205,"text":"have triple the lifetime risk\nof heart disease and lung cancer"},{"time":34292,"text":"and a 20-year difference\nin life expectancy."},{"time":39911,"text":"And yet, doctors today are not trained\nin routine screening or treatment."},{"time":46203,"text":"Now, the exposure I'm talking about is\nnot a pesticide or a packaging chemical."},{"time":51558,"text":"It's childhood trauma."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54968,"text":"Okay. What kind of trauma\nam I talking about here?"},{"time":57686,"text":"I'm not talking about failing a test\nor losing a basketball game."},{"time":61995,"text":"I am talking about threats\nthat are so severe or pervasive"},{"time":66736,"text":"that they literally get under our skin\nand change our physiology:"},{"time":71333,"text":"things like abuse or neglect,"},{"time":73725,"text":"or growing up with a parent \nwho struggles with mental illness"},{"time":77495,"text":"or substance dependence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79887,"text":"Now, for a long time,"},{"time":81444,"text":"I viewed these things in the way \nI was trained to view them,"},{"time":84441,"text":"either as a social problem --\nrefer to social services --"},{"time":88533,"text":"or as a mental health problem --\nrefer to mental health services."},{"time":94088,"text":"And then something happened\nto make me rethink my entire approach."},{"time":99776,"text":"When I finished my residency,"},{"time":101648,"text":"I wanted to go someplace\nwhere I felt really needed,"},{"time":105372,"text":"someplace where I could make a difference."},{"time":108530,"text":"So I came to work for\nCalifornia Pacific Medical Center,"},{"time":111646,"text":"one of the best private hospitals\nin Northern California,"},{"time":115472,"text":"and together, we opened a clinic\nin Bayview-Hunters Point,"},{"time":120000,"text":"one of the poorest, most underserved\nneighborhoods in San Francisco."},{"time":124263,"text":"Now, prior to that point,"},{"time":126118,"text":"there had been only\none pediatrician in all of Bayview"},{"time":128980,"text":"to serve more than 10,000 children,"},{"time":132423,"text":"so we hung a shingle, and we were able\nto provide top-quality care"},{"time":137072,"text":"regardless of ability to pay."},{"time":139057,"text":"It was so cool. We targeted\nthe typical health disparities:"},{"time":143219,"text":"access to care, immunization rates,\nasthma hospitalization rates,"},{"time":148026,"text":"and we hit all of our numbers."},{"time":150183,"text":"We felt very proud of ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":153446,"text":"But then I started noticing\na disturbing trend."},{"time":156627,"text":"A lot of kids were being\nreferred to me for ADHD,"},{"time":160517,"text":"or Attention Deficit\nHyperactivity Disorder,"},{"time":163514,"text":"but when I actually did\na thorough history and physical,"},{"time":168396,"text":"what I found was that\nfor most of my patients,"},{"time":171595,"text":"I couldn't make a diagnosis of ADHD."},{"time":175264,"text":"Most of the kids I was seeing\nhad experienced such severe trauma"},{"time":180834,"text":"that it felt like something else\nwas going on."},{"time":184224,"text":"Somehow I was missing something important."}]},{"cues":[{"time":189516,"text":"Now, before I did my residency,\nI did a master's degree in public health,"},{"time":193317,"text":"and one of the things that they teach you\nin public health school"},{"time":196410,"text":"is that if you're a doctor"},{"time":198295,"text":"and you see 100 kids\nthat all drink from the same well,"},{"time":202079,"text":"and 98 of them develop diarrhea,"},{"time":205477,"text":"you can go ahead\nand write that prescription"},{"time":207763,"text":"for dose after dose\nafter dose of antibiotics,"},{"time":212092,"text":"or you can walk over and say,\n\"What the hell is in this well?\""},{"time":217915,"text":"So I began reading everything that\nI could get my hands on"},{"time":221708,"text":"about how exposure to adversity"},{"time":224262,"text":"affects the developing brains\nand bodies of children."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227741,"text":"And then one day,\nmy colleague walked into my office,"},{"time":231646,"text":"and he said, \"Dr. Burke,\nhave you seen this?\""},{"time":236900,"text":"In his hand was a copy\nof a research study"},{"time":240902,"text":"called the Adverse Childhood\nExperiences Study."},{"time":244569,"text":"That day changed my clinical practice\nand ultimately my career."}]},{"cues":[{"time":252465,"text":"The Adverse Childhood Experiences Study"},{"time":254573,"text":"is something that everybody\nneeds to know about."},{"time":257805,"text":"It was done by Dr. Vince Felitti at Kaiser\nand Dr. Bob Anda at the CDC,"},{"time":263136,"text":"and together, they asked 17,500 adults\nabout their history of exposure"},{"time":271334,"text":"to what they called \"adverse \nchildhood experiences,\" or ACEs."},{"time":276911,"text":"Those include physical, emotional,\nor sexual abuse;"},{"time":280838,"text":"physical or emotional neglect;"},{"time":284764,"text":"parental mental illness,\nsubstance dependence, incarceration;"},{"time":287858,"text":"parental separation or divorce;"},{"time":290637,"text":"or domestic violence."},{"time":293172,"text":"For every yes, you would get\na point on your ACE score."},{"time":297608,"text":"And then what they did"},{"time":299116,"text":"was they correlated these ACE scores\nagainst health outcomes."},{"time":304836,"text":"What they found was striking."},{"time":307673,"text":"Two things:"},{"time":308968,"text":"Number one, ACEs are incredibly common."},{"time":313230,"text":"Sixty-seven percent of the population\nhad at least one ACE,"},{"time":320034,"text":"and 12.6 percent, one in eight,\nhad four or more ACEs."},{"time":326692,"text":"The second thing that they found"},{"time":328971,"text":"was that there was\na dose-response relationship"},{"time":332433,"text":"between ACEs and health outcomes:"},{"time":337033,"text":"the higher your ACE score,\nthe worse your health outcomes."},{"time":340952,"text":"For a person with an ACE score\nof four or more,"},{"time":344203,"text":"their relative risk of chronic\nobstructive pulmonary disease"},{"time":347895,"text":"was two and a half times that\nof someone with an ACE score of zero."},{"time":353096,"text":"For hepatitis, it was also\ntwo and a half times."},{"time":356370,"text":"For depression, it was\nfour and a half times."},{"time":359690,"text":"For suicidality, it was 12 times."},{"time":363123,"text":"A person with an ACE score\nof seven or more"},{"time":366288,"text":"had triple the lifetime risk\nof lung cancer"},{"time":370858,"text":"and three and a half times the risk\nof ischemic heart disease,"},{"time":374829,"text":"the number one killer\nin the United States of America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379124,"text":"Well, of course this makes sense."},{"time":381887,"text":"Some people looked at this data\nand they said, \"Come on."},{"time":386554,"text":"You have a rough childhood,\nyou're more likely to drink and smoke"},{"time":391376,"text":"and do all these things\nthat are going to ruin your health."},{"time":394191,"text":"This isn't science.\nThis is just bad behavior.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":398486,"text":"It turns out this is exactly\nwhere the science comes in."},{"time":403725,"text":"We now understand\nbetter than we ever have before"},{"time":408379,"text":"how exposure to early adversity"},{"time":411631,"text":"affects the developing brains\nand bodies of children."},{"time":414719,"text":"It affects areas like\nthe nucleus accumbens,"},{"time":417505,"text":"the pleasure and reward\ncenter of the brain"},{"time":420036,"text":"that is implicated\nin substance dependence."},{"time":422682,"text":"It inhibits the prefrontal cortex,"},{"time":425404,"text":"which is necessary for impulse control\nand executive function,"},{"time":429461,"text":"a critical area for learning."},{"time":431528,"text":"And on MRI scans,"},{"time":433216,"text":"we see measurable differences\nin the amygdala,"},{"time":437204,"text":"the brain's fear response center."},{"time":440246,"text":"So there are real neurologic reasons"},{"time":443766,"text":"why folks exposed\nto high doses of adversity"},{"time":447296,"text":"are more likely to engage\nin high-risk behavior,"},{"time":450593,"text":"and that's important to know."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452497,"text":"But it turns out that even if you don't\nengage in any high-risk behavior,"},{"time":458116,"text":"you're still more likely\nto develop heart disease or cancer."},{"time":464101,"text":"The reason for this has to do with\nthe hypothalamic–pituitary–adrenal axis,"},{"time":470027,"text":"the brain's and body's\nstress response system"},{"time":473696,"text":"that governs our fight-or-flight response."},{"time":477476,"text":"How does it work?"},{"time":479431,"text":"Well, imagine you're walking\nin the forest and you see a bear."},{"time":483169,"text":"Immediately, your hypothalamus\nsends a signal to your pituitary,"},{"time":487326,"text":"which sends a signal \nto your adrenal gland that says,"},{"time":489927,"text":"\"Release stress hormones!\nAdrenaline! Cortisol!\""},{"time":493478,"text":"And so your heart starts to pound,"},{"time":496099,"text":"Your pupils dilate, your airways open up,"},{"time":498234,"text":"and you are ready to either\nfight that bear or run from the bear."},{"time":504482,"text":"And that is wonderful"},{"time":506798,"text":"if you're in a forest\nand there's a bear."},{"time":510289,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":512843,"text":"But the problem is what happens\nwhen the bear comes home every night,"},{"time":518256,"text":"and this system is activated\nover and over and over again,"},{"time":523904,"text":"and it goes from being\nadaptive, or life-saving,"},{"time":528408,"text":"to maladaptive, or health-damaging."},{"time":532533,"text":"Children are especially sensitive\nto this repeated stress activation,"},{"time":538036,"text":"because their brains and bodies\nare just developing."},{"time":542000,"text":"High doses of adversity not only affect\nbrain structure and function,"},{"time":548075,"text":"they affect the developing immune system,"},{"time":551301,"text":"developing hormonal systems,"},{"time":554144,"text":"and even the way our DNA\nis read and transcribed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560413,"text":"So for me, this information\nthrew my old training out the window,"},{"time":564871,"text":"because when we understand\nthe mechanism of a disease,"},{"time":568818,"text":"when we know not only\nwhich pathways are disrupted, but how,"},{"time":573555,"text":"then as doctors, it is our job\nto use this science"},{"time":578216,"text":"for prevention and treatment."},{"time":580845,"text":"That's what we do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582728,"text":"So in San Francisco, we created\nthe Center for Youth Wellness"},{"time":586791,"text":"to prevent, screen and heal the impacts\nof ACEs and toxic stress."},{"time":592224,"text":"We started simply with routine screening\nof every one of our kids"},{"time":596807,"text":"at their regular physical,"},{"time":598334,"text":"because I know that if my patient \nhas an ACE score of 4,"},{"time":603038,"text":"she's two and a half times as likely\nto develop hepatitis or COPD,"},{"time":607595,"text":"she's four and half times as likely\nto become depressed,"},{"time":610497,"text":"and she's 12 times as likely\nto attempt to take her own life"},{"time":614560,"text":"as my patient with zero ACEs."},{"time":616860,"text":"I know that when she's in my exam room."},{"time":620249,"text":"For our patients who do screen positive,"},{"time":623013,"text":"we have a multidisciplinary treatment team\nthat works to reduce the dose of adversity"},{"time":628235,"text":"and treat symptoms using best practices,\nincluding home visits, care coordination,"},{"time":634118,"text":"mental health care, nutrition,"},{"time":638032,"text":"holistic interventions, and yes,\nmedication when necessary."},{"time":642747,"text":"But we also educate parents\nabout the impacts of ACEs and toxic stress"},{"time":647436,"text":"the same way you would for covering\nelectrical outlets, or lead poisoning,"},{"time":652946,"text":"and we tailor the care\nof our asthmatics and our diabetics"},{"time":656886,"text":"in a way that recognizes that they may\nneed more aggressive treatment,"},{"time":661344,"text":"given the changes to their hormonal\nand immune systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665771,"text":"So the other thing that happens\nwhen you understand this science"},{"time":669863,"text":"is that you want to shout it\nfrom the rooftops,"},{"time":672861,"text":"because this isn't just an issue\nfor kids in Bayview."},{"time":677191,"text":"I figured the minute\nthat everybody else heard about this,"},{"time":680825,"text":"it would be routine screening,\nmulti-disciplinary treatment teams,"},{"time":684308,"text":"and it would be a race to the most\neffective clinical treatment protocols."},{"time":689105,"text":"Yeah. That did not happen."},{"time":693225,"text":"And that was a huge learning for me."},{"time":696080,"text":"What I had thought of as simply\nbest clinical practice"},{"time":700887,"text":"I now understand to be a movement."},{"time":705125,"text":"In the words of Dr. Robert Block,"},{"time":707475,"text":"the former President\nof the American Academy of Pediatrics,"},{"time":711176,"text":"\"Adverse childhood experiences"},{"time":714128,"text":"are the single greatest\nunaddressed public health threat"},{"time":719138,"text":"facing our nation today.\""},{"time":721387,"text":"And for a lot of people,\nthat's a terrifying prospect."},{"time":726033,"text":"The scope and scale of the problem\nseems so large that it feels overwhelming"},{"time":731838,"text":"to think about how we might approach it."},{"time":734462,"text":"But for me, that's actually\nwhere the hopes lies,"},{"time":738869,"text":"because when we have the right framework,"},{"time":741533,"text":"when we recognize this to be\na public health crisis,"},{"time":746790,"text":"then we can begin to use the right \ntool kit to come up with solutions."},{"time":751794,"text":"From tobacco to lead poisoning \nto HIV/AIDS,"},{"time":755522,"text":"the United States actually has\nquite a strong track record"},{"time":760535,"text":"with addressing public health problems,"},{"time":763439,"text":"but replicating those successes\nwith ACEs and toxic stress"},{"time":768942,"text":"is going to take determination\nand commitment,"},{"time":773539,"text":"and when I look at what\nour nation's response has been so far,"},{"time":777511,"text":"I wonder,"},{"time":779355,"text":"why haven't we taken this more seriously?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":783154,"text":"You know, at first I thought\nthat we marginalized the issue"},{"time":786976,"text":"because it doesn't apply to us."},{"time":788900,"text":"That's an issue for those kids\nin those neighborhoods."},{"time":792198,"text":"Which is weird, because the data\ndoesn't bear that out."},{"time":796387,"text":"The original ACEs study\nwas done in a population"},{"time":800520,"text":"that was 70 percent Caucasian,"},{"time":803307,"text":"70 percent college-educated."},{"time":806465,"text":"But then, the more I talked to folks,"},{"time":809947,"text":"I'm beginning to think that maybe\nI had it completely backwards."},{"time":815334,"text":"If I were to ask\nhow many people in this room"},{"time":821278,"text":"grew up with a family member\nwho suffered from mental illness,"},{"time":825587,"text":"I bet a few hands would go up."},{"time":828053,"text":"And then if I were to ask how many folks\nhad a parent who maybe drank too much,"},{"time":833754,"text":"or who really believed that\nif you spare the rod, you spoil the child,"},{"time":839077,"text":"I bet a few more hands would go up."},{"time":842195,"text":"Even in this room, this is an issue\nthat touches many of us,"},{"time":847276,"text":"and I am beginning to believe\nthat we marginalize the issue"},{"time":850665,"text":"because it does apply to us."},{"time":853261,"text":"Maybe it's easier to see\nin other zip codes"},{"time":856121,"text":"because we don't want to look at it."},{"time":859024,"text":"We'd rather be sick."}]},{"cues":[{"time":862112,"text":"Fortunately, scientific advances\nand, frankly, economic realities"},{"time":868440,"text":"make that option less viable every day."},{"time":873524,"text":"The science is clear:"},{"time":875991,"text":"Early adversity dramatically affects\nhealth across a lifetime."},{"time":881870,"text":"Today, we are beginning to understand\nhow to interrupt the progression"},{"time":886632,"text":"from early adversity\nto disease and early death,"},{"time":890933,"text":"and 30 years from now,"},{"time":893458,"text":"the child who has a high ACE score"},{"time":895966,"text":"and whose behavioral symptoms\ngo unrecognized,"},{"time":899071,"text":"whose asthma management\nis not connected,"},{"time":901771,"text":"and who goes on to develop\nhigh blood pressure"},{"time":904975,"text":"and early heart disease or cancer"},{"time":907819,"text":"will be just as anomalous\nas a six-month mortality from HIV/AIDS."},{"time":912963,"text":"People will look at that situation\nand say, \"What the heck happened there?\""},{"time":918468,"text":"This is treatable."},{"time":920755,"text":"This is beatable."},{"time":923527,"text":"The single most important thing\nthat we need today"},{"time":927690,"text":"is the courage to look\nthis problem in the face"},{"time":931017,"text":"and say, this is real\nand this is all of us."},{"time":936089,"text":"I believe that we are the movement."}]},{"cues":[{"time":940826,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":942204,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}